\b \cf0 Concluding Comments
\b0 \
This paper questions whether generating wealth for shareholders is the sole role of the board, although apparently the research community is reluctant to state that there is no relationship between board and company performance. \
In practice, it cannot be 100% assumed that directors just want to increase shareholder value. They often have to take a more nuanced approach, balancing value generation with long term risk and stability. \
Authors that an alternative question: Does good governance stop the destruction of shareholder value?\
Research might re-focus on the differences between failed and non-failed firms, to see if more insight can be gained from bankruptcy and company responses.\
